<item>
            <title>[LU-15851] Adjust niov checks for large MD</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15851</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;An LNet user can allocate a large contiguous MD. That MD can have &amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
LNET_MAX_IOV pages which causes some LNDs to assert on either niov&lt;br/&gt;
argument passed to lnd_recv() or the value stored in&lt;br/&gt;
lnet_msg::msg_niov. This is true even in cases where the actual&lt;br/&gt;
transfer size is &amp;lt;= LNET_MTU and will not exceed limits in the LNDs.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
